portItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527880\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527880\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 25, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gjq1665702884133.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gjq1665702884133.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gjq1665702884133.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gjq1665702884133\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">ub \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set the maximum Uniface message buffer, expressed in bytes. Uniface segments the data to be sent into chunks of this size.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"gjq1665702884133__topic_d32420e1_d32421e1_d32422e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gjq1665702884133__p_d32423e1_d32424e1_d32425e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$TCP_PARAMS</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ub</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <var class=\"keyword varname\">MaximumMessageBuffer</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gjq1665702884133__section_rxf_cv3_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d608802e72\">Arguments</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gjq1665702884133__p_d32429e1_d32430e1_d32431e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">MaximumMessageBuffer</var>—size of data segment that Uniface presents to\n            the TCP connector for a single operation. Allowed values are <code class=\"ph codeph\">256</code>\n            through <code class=\"ph codeph\">8192</code>. The default is <code class=\"ph codeph\">4096</code> .</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gjq1665702884133__section_fhr_cv3_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d608802e93\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gjq1665702884133__p_d32435e1_d32436e1_d32437e1\">Set this option to a consistent value in all\n            assignment files.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gjq1665702884133__section_q3c_dv3_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d608802e102\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gjq1665702884133__p_d32441e1_d32442e1_d32443e1\">If the data to be sent is larger than the message\n            buffer, Uniface segments the data and calls the TCP driver for each segment. You can\n            adjust the size of the message buffer using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ub</span> option.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Consider using a lower value on slow, poor quality connections.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gjq1665702884133__p_d32447e1_d32448e1_d32449e1\">When a connection is made, a negotiation takes place\n            to establish this buffer size, and the lowest value is used. If you want to increase the\n            value, you should set this option consistently in all assignment files. The value can be\n            decreased for an individual client or server in its own assignment file.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gsj1665702882214.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>n</a><p>Determines whether the Nagle algorithm is used to bundle data packets into larger network packets before they are sent.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527880\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527880\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ub Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 25, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 ub Set the maximum Uniface message buffer, expressed in bytes. Uniface segments the data to be sent into chunks of this size. USYS$TCP_PARAMS { = } ub { = } MaximumMessageBuffer Arguments MaximumMessageBuffer —size of data segment that Uniface presents to the TCP connector for a single operation. Allowed values are 256 through 8192 . The default is 4096 . Use Set this option to a consistent value in all assignment files. Description If the data to be sent is larger than the message buffer, Uniface segments the data and calls the TCP driver for each segment. You can adjust the size of the message buffer using the ub option. Consider using a lower value on slow, poor quality connections. When a connection is made, a negotiation takes place to establish this buffer size, and the lowest value is used. If you want to increase the value, you should set this option consistently in all assignment files. The value can be decreased for an individual client or server in its own assignment file. Related Links n Determines whether the Nagle algorithm is used to bundle data packets into larger network packets before they are sent. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}